    category: "bioinformatics",
    summary: "Three freshly surfaced, novel Brown Biotech signals from the 2026-07-09 06:00 KST watcher scan (107 hits collected_at 2026-07-08 UTC; all three primary signals are novel versus yesterday's id:36 digest and absent from the last five sampleDigests). (1) TNBC CD45+ immune atlas across primary + sentinel + axillary lymph node (GSE328275, n=28 Homo sapiens scRNA-seq, pdat 12 days ago, the freshest score-9 single-cell dissection of regional immune-architecture routing in treatment-naive triple-negative breast cancer in the current scan, a direct input for Brown Biotech TNBC + tumor-immunology + metastasis-routing lane where triple-negative breast cancer remains the highest-unmet-need breast-cancer subtype with limited targeted-therapy options and ~30% distant-metastasis rate within 3 years). (2) Genomic and spatial transcriptomics identify fibroblast-associated microenvironment in early mycosis fungoides progression (GSE337336, n=16 Homo sapiens CosMx dataset, pdat 2026/07/07 = 2 days ago, the FRESHEST score-9 hit in the current scan and a direct bioinformatics / spatial + open-science + anti-fibrotic input for Brown Biotech cutaneous-T-cell-lymphoma + fibroblast-microenvironment lane where mycosis fungoides is the most-common cutaneous T-cell lymphoma and early progression carries a 5-year disease-specific survival of <50% with no validated molecular biomarkers). (3) Ferritin-mediated iron homeostasis regulates fibroblast activation and shapes post-infarction cardiac remodeling (GSE330351, n=9 Mus musculus single-cell + spatial, pdat 2026/06/30 = 9 days ago, a direct longevity / anti-fibrotic / cardio input for Brown Biotech post-MI cardiac-fibrosis lane where ferritin heavy-chain (Fth1) + ferroptosis-resistance has emerged as a tractable iron-handling axis in cardiac-fibroblast activation and a new target nomination beyond the canonical TGF-beta + collagen + alpha-SMA axis).",
